{
  "_comment": [
    "Viam Fragment template for consolidated TPS truck fleet deployment.",
    "",
    "Each truck has a single Pi 5 running all three modules:",
    "  - plc-sensor: Modbus TCP to Click PLC (TPS production monitoring)",
    "  - cell-sensor: Staubli REST + Apera socket (robot cell monitoring)",
    "  - j1939-sensor: CAN bus J1939 (truck engine diagnostics, listen-only)",
    "",
    "How to use:",
    "  1. In app.viam.com → Fragments → Create Fragment",
    "  2. Paste this JSON as the fragment config",
    "  3. For each truck machine, go to Config → Fragments → Add Fragment",
    "  4. Override the 'host' attribute with the truck's PLC IP address",
    "",
    "Per-truck overrides (set in machine config after adding fragment):",
    "  - components.plc-monitor.attributes.host  → truck's PLC IP (required)",
    "  - services.data-manager.attributes.tags   → add truck-specific tags",
    "",
    "Prerequisites on each Pi 5:",
    "  - CAN HAT installed with /boot/firmware/config.txt overlay",
    "  - can0 interface configured at 250kbps listen-only",
    "  - All three modules deployed to /opt/viam-modules/"
  ],
  "modules": [
    {
      "type": "local",
      "name": "plc-sensor-module",
      "executable_path": "/opt/viam-modules/plc-sensor/run.sh"
    },
    {
      "type": "local",
      "name": "cell-sensor-module",
      "executable_path": "/opt/viam-modules/cell-sensor/run.sh"
    },
    {
      "type": "local",
      "name": "j1939-truck-sensor",
      "executable_path": "/opt/viam-modules/j1939-sensor/exec.sh"
    }
  ],
  "components": [
    {
      "name": "plc-monitor",
      "api": "rdk:component:sensor",
      "model": "viam-staubli-apera-poc:monitor:plc-sensor",
      "attributes": {
        "host": "OVERRIDE_WITH_TRUCK_PLC_IP",
        "port": 502,
        "wheel_diameter_mm": 406.4,
        "offline_buffer_dir": "/home/pi/.viam/offline-buffer",
        "offline_buffer_max_mb": 50
      },
      "depends_on": [],
      "service_configs": [
        {
          "type": "data_manager",
          "attributes": {
            "capture_methods": [
              {
                "method": "Readings",
                "capture_frequency_hz": 1,
                "additional_params": {}
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "cell-monitor",
      "api": "rdk:component:sensor",
      "model": "viam-staubli-apera-poc:monitor:cell-sensor",
      "attributes": {
        "staubli_host": "192.168.0.254",
        "staubli_port": 80,
        "apera_host": "192.168.3.151",
        "apera_port": 14040,
        "apera_pipeline": "RAIV_pick_belt_1"
      },
      "depends_on": [],
      "service_configs": [
        {
          "type": "data_manager",
          "attributes": {
            "capture_methods": [
              {
                "method": "Readings",
                "capture_frequency_hz": 0.5,
                "additional_params": {}
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "truck-engine",
      "api": "rdk:component:sensor",
      "model": "ironsight:j1939-truck-sensor:can-sensor",
      "attributes": {
        "bitrate": 250000,
        "can_interface": "can0",
        "protocol": "j1939"
      },
      "depends_on": [],
      "service_configs": [
        {
          "type": "data_manager",
          "attributes": {
            "capture_methods": [
              {
                "method": "Readings",
                "capture_frequency_hz": 1,
                "additional_params": {}
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "services": [
    {
      "name": "data-manager",
      "type": "data_manager",
      "attributes": {
        "capture_dir": "/home/pi/.viam/capture",
        "sync_interval_mins": 0.1,
        "sync_disabled": false,
        "tags": ["tps-monitor", "cell-monitor", "truck-diagnostics", "OVERRIDE_WITH_TRUCK_ID"]
      }
    }
  ]
}
